law.text:
// EFFECTIVE UNTIL JUNE 30, 2015 PER CHAPTERS 624 AND 625 OF 2008 //
The power of the Secretary over plans, proposals, and projects of units in the Department does not include the power to disapprove or modify any decision or determination that the Commission makes under authority specifically delegated by law to the Commission.
The power of the Secretary to transfer by rule, regulation, or written directive any staff, functions, or funds of units in the Department does not apply to any staff, functions, or funds of the Commission.
